OL,5,Cblood
OL,7,FJersey's health department will offer
OL,8,Fmedical treatment to residents from
OL,9,Feffected areas with elevated levels of
OL,10,FPFAS in their blood - alongside
OL,11,Fadditional testing for at-risk groups.
OL,13,FThe government has outlined its formal
OL,14,Fresponse to address the potential
OL,15,Fhealth implications of the so-called
OL,16,F'forever chemicals' for those who have
OL,17,Flived or worked in the affected area.
OL,19,FFollowing blood testing by Public
OL,20,FHealth in 2022, 88 islanders were
OL,21,Ffound to have elevated PFAS levels.
