OL,5,Cblood
OL,7,FThose tested may now be offered
OL,8,Fcolesevelam: a cholesterollowering
OL,9,Fmedication proven to reduce PFAS
OL,10,Flevels in blood.
OL,12,FDirector of Public Health, Professor
OL,13,FPeter Bradley, says that this
OL,14,Fmedication works by "scooping up" PFAS
OL,15,Fin the body, which is then excreted.
OL,17,FIndividual medical assessments will be
OL,18,Fconducted by a PFAS-informed
OL,19,Fclinician, who may also offer
OL,20,Ftherapeutic phlebotomy as an
OL,21,Falternative intervention.
